<title>Top Ten Stats of Week -- Heritage</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<center><img src="/heritage/thf_log2.gif"></a>
<h2>The <i>Right</i> Numbers</h2>Compiled from the 1990 Long Form Census information<p>
<h3>Top Ten Facts for the Week of December 18</h3></center>
Note to users, the <b>Top Ten Facts</b> will resume the first week of January, 1996.
<p>
<hr><P>




<b>1.  Violent Crime Rate</b> for cities for cities over 250,000 in 1993:
<p><center>
		Highest: Atlanta, Georgia<br>
		Lowest:  Honolulu, Hawaii
</center><P>
Source: Bureau of Justice Statistics
<p><hr><p>

<b>2.</b> Question: "Are you in favor of the <b>death penalty</b> for a person convicted of murder?":
		<p><center>
<table border>
<tr>
<i><th>Year</i></th><th>Yes</th><th>No</th><th>No Opinion</th></i></tr>
<tr>
<td>1956</td><td>53%</td><td>34%</td><td>13%</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>1976</td><td>66%</td><td>26%</td><td>8%</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>1995</td><td>77%</td><td>13%</td><td>10%</td></tr>
</table>
</center><p>
Source: George Gallup, Jr., <i>The Gallup Poll</i>, (Los Angeles: The Gallup Organization, June 2, 1995), p. 2.
<p><hr><P>
<b>3.</b> Marital Status of  Nation's <b>3.8 million mothers receiving AFDC</b>:
<p><center>
		Never married: 		48%<br>
		Widowed/Divorced: 	23%<br>
		Husband separated, absent: 17%<br>
		<b>Marriage Intact: 		13%</b><br>
</center><p>
Source: U.S. Bureau of the Census.  Percentages do not sum to 100 due to rounding.
<p><hr><p>
<b>4.</b>  According to municipal elected officials,  the top two conditions that have <b>most deteriorated</b> in the last five years and are the <b>most important</b> to address in the next two are:<center><p>		1. Unfunded Mandates<br>				2. Violent Crime</center><p>Source: "The State of America's Cities: The Eleventh Annual Opinion Survey of Municipal Elected Officials", National League of Cities, January, 1995.<p><hr><p><b>5.</b> Persons convicted of offenses involving the <b>abuse of local, state or federal offices</b>: 
<p><center><table border><tr><i><th>Year</th><th>Convicted</th></i></tr><tr><td>1970</td><td>44</td></tr><tr><td>1980</td><td>552</td></tr><tr><td>1991</td><td>1,194</td></tr></table></center><p>Source: "Report to Congress on the Activities and Operations of the Public Integrity Section for 1991," Washington, DC: U.S. Department of Justice, 1992.<p><hr><p><b>6. Actual bombing incidents</b> in the U.S. known to police:
	<p><center>
<table border>
<tr><i>
<th>Year</th><th>Actual Bombings</th></i></tr>
<tr>
<td>1973</td><td>1,529</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>1983</td><td>589</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>1993</td><td>2,418</td></tr>
</table></center><p>
Source: "Bombing Incidents Known to Police," Bureau of Justice Statistics Sourcebook of Criminal Justice Statistics, 1994, Table 3.155.
<p><hr><p>
<b>7.</b>  Immigrants account for 4.7% of the United States' general population, but make up <b>only 4%</b> of the general prison population.
<p>
Source: Bureau of Justice Statistics, Survey of State Prison Inmates, 1991.  March, 1993.
<p><hr><p>
<b>8.  Social Security Payroll Tax</b>:
<p><center>
 
1937:  1%<br>
1960:  3%<br>
1980:  5.08%<br>
1995:  6.2%<br>
</center><p><hr><p>

<b>9.</b>   Average Number of  People served by Public Sewer in Each Congressional District: 175,356<br>
      Average Number of People served by Septic Tank in Each Congressional District: 56,585
<p>
Source: 1990 Census
<p><hr><p>

<b>10.</b>  Per Capita Utilization of Fruits and Vegetables in Pounds:
 <p><center>
<table border>
<tr><i>
<th>Year</th><th>Fruits</th><th>Vegetables</th></i></tr>
<tr>
<td>1970</td><td>79.1</td><td>88.1</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>1980</td><td>86.9</td><td>92.5</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>1990</td><td>92.2</td><td>113.3</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>1992</td><td>98.7</td><td>109.3</td></tr>
</table></center><p>
Source: Statistical Abstract of the United States, 1994.    Table #221
<p>
For more of <b>The <i>Right</i> Numbers</b>, check out the <a href="/heritage/cd_ranking/i-cdrank.html">Congressional District Ranking Book</a>.
