<title>Top Ten Stats of Week -- Heritage</title>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">

<center><img src="/heritage/thf_log2.gif"></a>

<h2>The <i>Right</i> Numbers</h2>Compiled from the 1990 Long Form Census information<p>

<h3>Top Ten Facts for Week of February 12, 1996</h3></center>

<p><hr><p>

<b>1.</b> Percentage of American adults who <b>write and mail a letter</b> during a given week: <p><center>28
</center><p>
<font size=-1">Source: Interactive Telecom</font>
<p><hr><p>

<b>2.</b> Number of <b>business establishments</b> in the U.S.: 
<p><center>
6,403,367
</center><p>
<font size="-1">Source:  County Business Patterns produced by the Census Bureau and is based on 1993.  It excludes most government employees, railroad employees and self-employed people</font>
<p><hr><p>
