<body><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg"><center>
<img src="/heritage/thf_log2.gif"></a>
<h2>The <i>Right</i> Numbers</h2>Compiled from the 1990 Long Form Census information<p>
<h3>Top Ten Conservative Stats for the Week of November 20</h3></center>

<hr><P>


<b>1.</b> Percentage of <b>state prisoners</b> serving a drug sentence<sup>1</sup>:
<p><center>

			1980:  6%<br>

			1993: 22%

</center><p>
<b>2.</b> Percentage of <b>federal prisoners</b> serving a drug sentence<sup>2</sup>:
<p><center>
			1980: 25%<br>
			1993: 60%
</center><p>
<b>3.</b> Highest and lowest percentages of <b>state education budgets</b> supported by federal government<sup>3</sup>:
<p><center>
			Highest: Mississippi	--  17%<br>
			Lowest:  New Hampshire 	--   2%<br>
			Average: 6.9%
</center><p>
<b>4. Black Median Family Income</b> fell under Carter, but increased under Reagan (1992 Dollars)<sup>4</sup>:
<p><center>
			1975: $21,916<br>
			1980: $21,606<br>
			1988: $22,924<br>

</center><p>
<b>5. Medicare Program Payments</b>, Total Hospital Insurance and/or Supplementary Medical Insurance<sup>5</sup>:
<p><center>
			1967:    $4.3 Billion<br>
			1993: $129.4 Billion
</center><p>

<b>6.</b> Size of <b>Yearly Deficit</b> at the end of Presidential Terms<sup>6</sup>:
<p><center>
			Carter 1980	- $  73.8 Billion<br>
			Reagan 1984	- $185.4 Billion<br>
			Reagan 1988	- $155.2 Billion<br>
			Bush 1992	- $290.4 Billion<br>
</center><p>
<b>7.</b> Percentage of Persons over 25 that have completed <b>4 or more years of college</b><sup>7</sup>:
<P><center>

			1960:	  7.7%<br>

			1970:	10.7%<br>

			1980:	16.2%<br>

			1990:	21.3%<br>

</center><p>
<b>8.</b> Percentage of U.S. adult resident population under some form of <b>correctional supervision</b> (prison, probation or parole)<sup>8</sup>:
<p><center>			
			1980: 1.1%<br>
			1993: 2.6%<br>
</center><p>
<b>9.</b> Average <b>Farm operator income</b> and percentage derived from off-farm sources<sup>9</sup>:
<p><center>
			1991 average total farm household income: $37,644<br>
			1991 average income from farming: $5,000<br>
			Income from off-farm sources: 85%<br>

</center><p>
<b>10.</b> Sales of <b>Vinyl Discs vs. Compact Discs</b><sup>10</sup>:
<p><center>
			1983 <br>
			Albums-LP's/EP's: 	209.6 million<br>
			Compact Discs: 		0.8 million<br>
			<p>
			1992<br>
			Albums-LP's/EP's: 	2.3 million<br>
			Compact Discs: 		407.5 million<br>
</center><p>
